node.text: In this video, I talk about how to listen without giving feedback and I answer a few Q&A’s.

node.title: Listening Without Offering Feedback and Q&A

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Never deny someone's pain because you didn't mean it. 
Stop telling people, "I didn't mean to hurt you.," when they express that they're hurt. 

Accept that you can unintentionally hurt others. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This might be hard to hear, but: There are typically two reasons people don't answer their phones That don't want to talk 2.They are unavailable Respect both @NEDRATAWWAB WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
People have the right to be unavailable, and they have the right not to answer when they don't want to talk. 

Respect boundaries.

#nedratawwab #setboundariesfindpeace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Relationship maturity is looking at the whole person, good and bad, and determining based on who they are if you want to be in a relationship with them @NEDRATAWWAE WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
One of these best parts of adulthood good is choosing how you want to live. You can decide what you're willing to deal with or not. 

We can't change people. You either like who they are, or you don't like who they are. 

Ask yourself:
If I can't change anything, is this what I want? 
Can I tolerate the things that bother me about the person?
Are the flaws deal breakers?
What am I willing to accept? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: Trying to understand why something happened might get in the way of you responding and healing from what happened- knowing why is secondary to you taking action. Years will pass, and you may not know why. Feel what you need to without getting to the bottom of things. Heal without putting together the missing pieces. Repeat After Me: My part is responding to what happened, not immediately filling in the missing pieces, trying to understand why me or why this. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Perhaps knowing why will give you comfort, but it will never erase what happened. As you gather more information, respond to what you already know. 

Your power is in choosing how you want to respond. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Things to let go of: people who have let go of you how things should be controlling others redoing the past predicting the future convincing people to be like you stuff that no longer works Make room for more by releasing things you can't control or change. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Practice releasing as a way to welcome new things in things into your life. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist in Charlotte, North Carolina. May be an image of text.

node.text:
For many of us, it takes time before we are willing to accept things that we want to be different. 

With acceptance there is peace because you are no longer fighting reality. If there is something that you struggle to accept, figure what’s within your control and develop strategies to manage what you can. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'When someone chooses to end a relationship with a family member, it is not an easy decision or based on one thing. Often the relationship has ended after many rounds of forgiveness and trying to make the relationship work. When you encounter someone who has decided to let go of a relationship that disturbed their peace, caused them mental or emotional stress, offer them grace instead of your opinion. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Perhaps there is a history that you do not understand. 

Support people who are making choices in the best interest of their mental health. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: Burnout is not a symbol of how hardworking, nice, or productive you are. Running yourself to the ground is not a way to show people how much you care. Burnout is a sign of unhealthy perimeters with yourself and others. Repeat After Me: Me: Overextending myself is not healthy for me. It's beneficial for me to have limits with myself and others. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Burnout is an indicator of unhealthy perimeters around your time and energy. 

#nedranuggets #setboundariesfindpeace

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Perhaps people aren't bougie, funny acting, or standoffish; instead, they might be introverted, living differently than you, or enjoying their own world. You will not understand everything about other people. And when you don't understand attempt to learn more without judging. Judgment is most prevalent when we think other people should be like us. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Embrace people being different by not judging their differences negatively. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Remember This: Endings don't require drama or toxic behaviors. You can end something because it's not what you want, it doesn't fit where you're going, you're tired of trying to make it work, your needs have changed, or you can no longer accept what is happening You don't have to wait for a major offense to let things go. It's okay to bow out gracefully. Sometimes peace is more important than giving someone a piece of your mind. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
It's possible to gently let go. ⁣⁣⁣

Go in peace. 
⁣
{Soft Endings}⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣#nedranuggets ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Forgiveness is a choice you make, and it doesn't require you to return to unhealthy situations. If the situation, the person, or you have not changed, you will be returning to an unhealthy situation. 

Change is the highest form of apology and also a reason to forgive and return. 

“Just because someone is sorry does not mean they have changed.” ~Dr. Henry Cloud 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I knew I was maturing when I realized: @NEDRATAWWAB Many of the issues that had in my relationships were the result of unhealthy boundaries. It wasn't my job to rescue people and meddle in their problems. Gossiping is not the only way to connect in conversation. Some people won't change in a time frame that works for what I want for my life. I was getting upset with people for being themselves (I was expecting something different from people who hadn't changed.) Asking for help is healthy, not weak. There are some things that may not get over. www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
When presented with helpful information, maturity is changing your perspective, adhering to the life lessons you've learned through trial and error, and growing from watching others. Also, maturity is embodying your beliefs. 

How have you noticed yourself maturing? 

#nedranuggets
